            . Q. Tell us what you saw of this transaction - A. I saw him putting glasses in his pocket two or three times; in consequence of that I told the foreman; he first said the glass were his own, afterwards he said he was sorry for it; after my brother sent for the constable he said lord have mercy upon me.</p>
               <p>Q. How many glasses were taken out of his pocket. - A. Eleven.</p>
